HEADWORD: Sorel
<hw>Sor"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A diminutive. See
<er>Sore</er> reddish brown.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A young buck in the third year. See the Note under
<er>Buck</er>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A yellowish or reddish brown color;
sorrel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sorely</ent>⟦br⟧
